The Vice President, Mike Pence, visited the U.S. Embassy in Rome, Italy, and expressed his gratitude to military spouses for their service to the country. Pence assured the spouses that the Trump administration is committed to supporting their lives and careers. He also highlighted the strong security partnership between the United States and Italy and praised the 30,000 American military personnel and their families living and serving in Italy. Pence concluded his remarks by thanking the military spouses for their sacrifices and service to the nation.